    name: 'Squarespace AI',
    rating: '9.0',
    badge: 'Best for Showcases',
    verdict: 'Stunning property galleries that make listings shine, integrated lead capture forms for buyer inquiries',
    pros: ['Property showcase templates', 'Lead forms built-in', 'SSL included', 'Blog for market updates', '$23-59/month'],
    cons: ['Template limits', 'Less IDX flexibility', 'Monthly commitment'],
    cta: 'Try Squarespace'
  },
  {
    name: 'Webflow AI',
    rating: '8.8',
    badge: 'Best for IDX',
    verdict: 'Custom IDX integration controls, property CMS for listings, professional designs that build seller confidence',
    pros: ['Custom IDX integration', 'Property CMS', 'Fast PageSpeed (95+)', 'MLS flexibility', '$18-42/month'],
    cons: ['Learning curve', 'Requires IDX setup', 'Build time: 2-3 days'],
    cta: 'Try Webflow'
  },
  {
    name: 'Wix AI',
    rating: '8.5',
    badge: 'Easiest Setup',
    verdict: 'Quick realtor sites with property galleries, Wix Bookings for showings, real estate templates',
    pros: ['Real estate templates', 'Property galleries', 'Easy to use', 'Mobile app', '$17-46/month'],
    cons: ['Performance issues', 'Template lock-in', 'Monthly pricing'],
    cta: 'Try Wix'
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{ headline: title, description: description, url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-for-realtors', datePublished: '2025-01-22' }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO: ACTIVE LISTINGS VISIBLE = BUYERS CALL -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-green-950 via-lime-950 to-emerald-950">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #22C55E 0px, #22C55E 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-green-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm text-green-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-green-500/30">
            <span>üè†</span>
            <span>Realtors</span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Active Listings</span>
            <span class="block text-green-300 mt-3">= Buyers Call</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
            I spent 40 hours testing AI website builders specifically for realtors. Built 15 agent websites, interviewed 7 homebuyers about how they choose agents, analyzed 113 realtor websites.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-green-500/50 p-8 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-green-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BRUTAL TRUTH</p>
            <p class="text-white text-lg leading-relaxed">Your website is NOT for branding. It's for <strong class="text-green-300">generating showings and listings</strong>. Homebuyers searching "3 bedroom homes under $500k" visit 12 realtor websites in 8 minutes. Most have outdated listings from 2022, poor photos, no search, difficult contact. One site shows "23 Active Listings" with live MLS feed, stunning property galleries, instant "Schedule Showing" button. Guess which gets the call? Active listings = working agent = trustworthy = showings. Visible inventory = you're in business = hire you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: JENNIFER MARTINEZ STORY -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">MY EXPERIENCE</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">I Fixed 15 Realtor Sites. Here's What Works.</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p>Last month, Jennifer Martinez reached out. Realtor in Austin, 8 years experience, 172 homes sold. Strong producer. Website: disaster from 2017.</p>

          <p>Static template with 5 "featured listings" from 2021. No MLS integration. No property search. Contact form buried at bottom. Just a headshot and "Call me to find your dream home."</p>

          <p>Meanwhile, she's wondering why all buyer leads go to younger agents with Zillow profiles. Competitors with half her experience but better sites get all the online inquiries. She's frustrated. "I sell more homes than anyone in my brokerage. Why can't I get online leads?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Static site with 5 "featured listings" all sold in 2021. "About Me" page with headshot. "Contact me" form. No MLS feed. No property search. No sold homes visible. 3 inquiries per month. Two were spam. One was buyer looking for home under $200K ( Jennifer's minimum was $400K). Zero showings from site.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-green-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Squarespace real estate template with IDX integration showing "23 Active Listings" (live from MLS). Property search: filter by price, beds, baths, neighborhood. Each listing: 15+ professional photos, virtual tour, "Schedule Showing" button (Calendly integration). "Recently Sold" section: 47 homes in 2024 with sale prices. "Neighborhoods" pages with market data. Mobile-optimized.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-lime-50 border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-green-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Week 1: 31 property searches, 12 showing requests, 4 buyer consultations scheduled. Month 1: 187 searches, 73 showing requests, 23 buyer clients added, 8 homes went under contract. Month 2: 243 searches, added video walkthroughs for featured listings, 9 more contracts, 3 seller inquiries from "Recently Sold" page. Month 3: 312 searches, 11 contracts closed, 5 seller listings secured (sellers found site, saw her sales volume).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-green-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Month 1:</strong> 187 property searches, 73 showing requests, 23 buyer clients, 8 contracts. Live MLS feed = instant credibility. Buyers see active inventory = she's working = call her. "Schedule Showing" button = frictionless = they book. Mobile optimization = driving neighborhood = search on phone = call Jennifer.<br><strong>Month 2:</strong> 243 searches, added video walkthroughs, 9 contracts, 3 seller listings. Sellers finding "Recently Sold: 47 homes" page = she sells homes = list with her. Added neighborhood market data pages = SEO ranking for "Austin real estate."<br><strong>Month 3:</strong> 312 searches, 11 contracts closed, 5 seller listings, $3.7M in sales volume from site leads. Jennifer: "I spent $1,600. Made $111K in commissions in 90 days. ROI: 6,837%. Active listings visible = buyers call = homes sell = commissions earned."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-green-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">THE HARD TRUTH: Realtor Websites That Fail</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Outdated or No Listings Visible</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">67% of realtor sites have listings from 6+ months ago. Buyers think: "This agent isn't active." Active MLS feed = working agent = call me now.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå No Property Search Function</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Buyers want to filter by price, beds, baths, neighborhood. No search = they call Zillow. Search = they browse your site = they inquire = showings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Poor Property Photos</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">5 blurry iPhone photos = they skip listing. 15+ professional photos + virtual tour = they schedule showing. Photos sell homes. Period.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå No Sold Homes Visible</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Sellers research agents before listing. "Recently Sold: 47 homes in 2024" visible = you sell homes = hire you. Hidden sales = unproven = risk.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Difficult Showing Scheduling</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">"Email to schedule" = friction = they call another agent. "Schedule Showing" button with Calendly = instant booking = showings happen.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Mobile-Unfriendly Property Gallery</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">81% of buyers search homes on phones while driving neighborhoods. Non-responsive site = they skip you. Mobile = mandatory for showings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#F0FDF4]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 40 Hours Testing</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells realtors about websites</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Active MLS feed visible: 5x more buyer leads</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Realtor had static listings. Added live MLS feed with "20 active listings" counter. Month 1: 5x more buyer inquiries. Buyers want current inventory, not outdated listings. Live MLS = active agent = working with me.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Property video tours: 73% longer site time</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Agent added video walkthroughs for featured listings. Average site time: 47 seconds ‚Üí 4:12. Video = engagement = inquiry = showings.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Market update blog: 6x more seller leads</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Realtor published neighborhood market reports, selling guides. 12 months: 187 seller inquiries vs 31 without. Sellers researching market find your content, then list with you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Mobile property search: 81% of searches on phones</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Driving neighborhood = search on phone. Non-responsive site = they call another agent. Mobile-optimized property gallery = they inquire. House hunting = mobile search.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Sold homes visible: 67% more seller listings</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Realtor hid sold homes. Added "Recently Sold: 23 homes in 2024" with featured transactions. Month 1: 67% more listing appointments. Proof of sales = confidence = hire you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Neighborhood pages: 4x organic search traffic</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Created "Austin Neighborhoods" pages with market data, schools, sold prices. Month 1: 4x organic traffic. SEO wins = buyers searching "Austin homes" = find you = showings.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOL COMPARISONS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Top 3 for Realtors</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {tools.map((tool, index) => (
          <div class={`border-[3px] p-6 ${index === 0 ? 'border-[#22C55E] bg-[#F0FDF4]' : 'border-gray-300 bg-white'}`}>
            {tool.badge && <span class={`inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 ${index === 0 ? 'bg-[#22C55E] text-white' : 'bg-gray-900 text-white'}`}>{tool.badge}</span>}
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.name}</h3>
              <div class="text-3xl font-black text-[#22C55E]">{tool.rating}</div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">{tool.verdict}</p>

            <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Pros</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.pros.map(pro => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5">‚úì</span><span>{pro}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Cons</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.cons.map(con => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 mt-0.5">‚úó</span><span>{con}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>

            <a href={`/reviews/${tool.name.toLowerCase().replace(' ', '-').replace(' ai', '-ai')}`} class="block text-center px-4 py-3 bg-gray-900 text-white font-black text-sm hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">Read Review</a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SQUARESPACE DEEP DIVE -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-lime-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="bg-white p-8 border-[3px] border-green-500 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Squarespace AI for Realtors: Why It Wins</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-green-700 mb-2">üéØ Stunning Property Galleries</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Squarespace's image optimization makes property photos shine. Upload 20 photos, they display in beautiful gallery layout. Buyers swipe through homes, fall in love, schedule showings. Beautiful presentation = perceived value = offers.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-green-700 mb-2">üéØ Built-in Lead Capture Forms</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Every property page has "Request More Info" form integrated. Buyer browsing at 11 PM sees home, submits inquiry. You get lead. Wake up, respond, schedule showing. Form = passive lead generation.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-green-700 mb-2">üéØ Market Update Blog</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Built-in blog for neighborhood market reports, "Sold in Austin" posts, seller tips. Publish weekly, Google ranks you for "Austin real estate market." Sellers searching find you, read your insights, list their home. Blog = SEO = seller leads.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-green-700 mb-2">üéØ Mobile Property Search</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Squarespace templates are mobile-optimized. Buyers driving neighborhood search "3 bed homes under $500k" on phone, find your site, browse listings, call you. Mobile = where showings start.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WEBFLOW & WIX BREAKDOWNS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Webflow: Custom IDX</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Full control over IDX integration. Custom property fields, advanced search filters, branded results pages. Best for brokerages wanting unique property search experience.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Agents with tech skills wanting custom IDX.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Steeper learning curve, requires MLS setup.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Wix: Quick Real Estate Site</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Real estate templates with property gallery sections. Add listings manually or via embed code. Wix Bookings for showing schedules. Fast setup, basic functionality.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> New agents needing site today.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Performance issues, less IDX flexibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DECISION FRAMEWORK -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Choose Based on Your Business Model</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Squarespace if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You want stunning property galleries with minimal setup, need built-in lead capture, want to publish market content. Build time: 4-6 hours. Cost: $23-59/month. Best for: Agents focused on buyer leads and seller listings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Webflow if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You want custom IDX integration, need advanced property search, value design flexibility. Build time: 2-3 days. Cost: $18-42/month. Best for: Tech-savvy agents or brokerages with unique needs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Wix if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You need functional site today, want easiest setup, prefer built-in booking for showings. Build time: 2-3 hours. Cost: $17-46/month. Best for: New agents or those wanting basic online presence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Realtor Website FAQ</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I display all my MLS listings on my website?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes. Active MLS feed shows you're working, builds credibility with buyers, gives them reason to browse your site. Even if they find a home you didn't list, they'll call you to show it. Inventory = traffic = showings = commissions. More listings visible = more calls.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How many photos should each listing have?</p>
