        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I include video walkthroughs?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Absolutely. Video walkthroughs increase engagement 73%. Buyers watch 2-minute tour, see flow, envision living there, schedule showing. Video = emotional connection = serious buyer = stronger offer. Add to featured listings for maximum impact.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">What should I include on my "Recently Sold" page?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Every home you sold in past 12 months with: address (or neighborhood), sold price, days on market, before/after photos, client testimonial. Sellers research agents before listing. Proof of sales = confidence = hire you. Hide sales = unproven = they list with someone else.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I publish market update content?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes. Monthly neighborhood market reports ("Austin homes sold 7% above asking in January"), seller guides ("5 Pre-Listing Repairs That Return 10x"), buyer tips ("First-Time Homebuyer Mistakes to Avoid"). Content = SEO = sellers find you = list with you. Consistent publishing = authority = trust = calls.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How do I capture buyer leads on my website?</p>
